ABUJA â€“ President Muhammadu Buhari has condoled with family of former Chief of Naval Staff, Rear Admiral Ishaya Iko Ibrahim (Rtd), who served as Flag Officer Commanding Naval Training Command and Naval Western Command before reaching the peak of his career. The President said he joins friends and associates, particularly in the military hierarchy, in mourning the passing of the naval officer, whose meritorious service to the nation continues to inspire many officers, leaving a sustained legacy of loyalty, patriotism and gallantry. President Buhari also commiserated with the family and associates of former Head of the Directorate of Military Intelligence, Brig-Gen Ibrahim Sabo, whose contributions to the security structure and operations will always be remembered, particularly playing a significant role in counselling leaders after his retirement. Ugwuanyi Mourns Anthony Obi FCT State Minister Orders Clean Up Of Abuja Satellite Towns The President prayed that the Almighty God will receive the souls of the departed former military officers, and comfort their families.